      • addBuilders

        @NotNull
@Contract(value="_ -> !null")
public ListBuilder<T> addBuilders(@NotNull
                                          java.lang.Iterable<? extends Builder<? extends T>> elements)
        Add all of the given Builders, in order, as builders of element values to the end of the list.

        As with add(Builder), this does not invoke any of the builders immediately to build the element value. Each builder will be invoked once during a call to get().

        Parameters:
        elements - An Iterable of the builders to add.
        Returns:
        this object itself, for chaining convenience.
        See Also:
        addBuilders(Iterator), addBuilders(Builder[]), addAll(Iterable)

      • add

        @NotNull
@Contract(value="_ -> !null")
public ListBuilder<T> add(@NotNull
                                  Builder<? extends T> elementBuilder)
        Add the given Builder as a builder for the next item in the list. The builder is not invoked to build the value immediately, its Builder.get() method is invoked to build the element value only when this object's get() method is invoked to build a list of values.
        Parameters:
        elementBuilder - Builder for the element to put at the end of the current list of elements.
        Returns:
        this object itself, for chaining convenience.
